# Strategic Context Reference

Before writing copy, headlines, CTAs, or deciding page structure, always consult these files:

- `.cursor/context/positioning.md` — brand positioning, promise, differentiation
- `.cursor/context/icp.md` — ideal customer profile, awareness level, pain points
- `.cursor/context/tone-of-voice.md` — copy rules, what we sound like vs what we avoid
- `.cursor/context/site-architecture.md` — page map, roles, URL structure, content system
- `.cursor/context/kpi-map.md` — metrics per page, conversion flow

If these files have not been read in the current session and the task involves content, structure, or UX decisions, read them first.
